{"name":"Zunera","role":"Associate Professor, University of Warwick","tagline":"Researching policing, security and social order in the Global South.","bio":"Zunera is an Associate Professor at the University of Warwick working on criminology, law and socio-legal studies. Her research focuses on law enforcement, digitalisation, cybercrime, surveillance and urban (in)security, with a particular emphasis on South Asia and the Global South. She studied at SOAS and King's College London, and held postdoctoral and teaching positions at UCL.","portrait":"/portrait.webp","emailAcademic":"zoha.waseem@warwick.ac.uk","emailPersonal":"zoha.waseem@gmail.com","twitter":"https://twitter.com/ZohaWaseem","linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/zohawaseem/","interests":["Policing","Urban (in)security","Surveillance","Cybercrime","Digitalisation","Postcolonial criminology","South Asia"]}